# .adl-ignore file
# This file specifies which files should not be overwritten during generation operations.
# Files listed here typically contain implementations that users have completed.
#
# Patterns supported:
# - Exact file names: tools/agent_tool.go
# - Wildcards: *.go
# - Directory patterns: tools/*
# - Directories: build/
# - Comments: lines starting with #

# Add your own files to ignore here:
# my-custom-file.go
# config/secrets.yaml

Taskfile.yml
.gitattributes
Dockerfile

# Forked generator-owned file. The adl-cli template hardcodes a dependency
# version pin that is not derivable from agent.yaml, so a blind regenerate
# reverts the bump applied here by Dependabot / manual commits. Protect it so
# `task generate` keeps the bump intact (see issue #98):
#   - manifest.toml:  claude-code CLI pin (commit fe599c3)
# NOTE: infer.yml is intentionally NOT protected - it is regenerated so the
# pipeline stays in sync with the adl-cli template (infer-action pin comes
# from the template / an adl-cli bump, not from a fork here).
.flox/env/manifest.toml

tools/search_n8n_docs.go
tools/search_n8n_docs_test.go
tools/validate_n8n_workflow.go
tools/validate_n8n_workflow_test.go
.agents/skills/n8n-workflow-generation/
.agents/skills/n8n-workflow-validation/
